"We want justice, we want closure, we want healing, we want reconciliation, but first we have to get justice", he said.
"We cannot achieve healing and reconciliation until we get justice".
A coroner is laying a sheet over the body of one of the victims of the Moore-Ford lynching on July 27, 1946.
