The memo adds that if the departure from the White House were delayed, a second crew would be needed for the return flight due to the limited hours of duty.
The original flight crew was with the helicopter during the event, while the unit's security personnel remained on the ground with the aircraft during the time.
The records provided to TIME did not make it clear whether a second flight crew was ultimately needed.
The Hatch Act prohibits federal employees from using government property for political purposes.
