Trump conducted an investigation in February when the presidential plane was taxiing in the background of his first campaign rally in Melbourne, Florida, and his Twitter account is full of posts complaining about his predecessor's use of the presidential plane.
"The White House is excited about the Made In America show - which features products from all 50 states made by American workers with American materials", said White House Deputy Press Secretary Lindsay Walters.
HMX-1 crews frequently conduct training flights in the Washington area and the South Lawn to drop the US president at the White House with precision inches.
