Did PSG warn Barcelona about Neymar three years ago?
The La Liga side may regret their interest in Marco Verratti
Paris Saint-Germain will not relent in their pursuit of Neymar after making a £189 million offer to trigger his release clause, but did they warn Barcelona three years ago about the world record-breaking robbery?
The sensational approach has heated the summer transfer window as the Ligue 1 club is set to break the world record by more than double the previous mark, with Paul Pogba returning to Manchester United for £89m last season.
After his retirement, Neymar becomes the world's most expensive player and the highest paid professional athlete in the world.
Barcelona are angry about the way Neymar has forced his way out, although a source close to the Catalan board insists the club has always done its best to look after him since his arrival from Santos in 2013.
But was the world of football warned about this prospect by the PSG president three years ago?
When Manchester City expressed interest in signing Blaise Matuidi in 2014, Nasser Al-Khelaifi had a stern warning for any club that wanted to sign one of PSG's best players.
"I'm not worried because they know that if they touch one of our players, then we will be in opposition to them, we will contact their players", Al-Khelaifi said.
"We respect all clubs.
